data.chText: 不予考虑；摒弃；对…不屑一提
data.enText: to decide that sb/sth is not important and not worth thinking or talking about

data.chText: 我认为我们对他们的异议完全可以不予理会。
data.enText: I think we can safely dismiss their objections.

data.chText: 素食主义者不再被当作怪人。
data.enText: Vegetarians are no longer dismissed as cranks.

data.chText: 他认为民意测验毫无用处而不予考虑。
data.enText: He dismissed the opinion polls as worthless.

data.chText: 这建议不应当直接就被摒弃。
data.enText: The suggestion should not be dismissed out of hand (= without thinking about it) .

data.chText: 去除，消除，摒除（思想、感情等）
data.enText: to put thoughts or feelings out of your mind

data.chText: 她排除了恐惧，爬得更高了。
data.enText: Dismissing her fears, she climbed higher.
He dismissed her from his mind.
to officially remove sb from their job

data.chText: 她声称自己被无理免职。
data.enText: She claims she was unfairly dismissed from her post.

data.chText: 让（某人）离开；把（某人）打发走；解散
data.enText: to send sb away or allow them to leave
At 12 o'clock the class was dismissed.
to say that a trial or legal case should not continue, usually because there is not enough evidence
to end the innings of a player or team

simple_means.memory_skill: dis 加强 + miss 送，放出 → 不断把人送出 → 解散

means: 去除，消除，摒除(思想、感情等)

ex.chText: 那名教师被秘密开除了。
员工上班时间玩电脑游戏会遭到解雇。
ex.enText: Employees can be dismissed/fired/sacked for playing computer games at work.

synonyms.bx: 指正式解除某人的职务，常可与 fire，sack 换用。

ex.chText: 该公司周四宣布计划裁员180人。
ex.enText: The company announced Thursday their plan to axe 180 employees.
Vera has been axed from the team.

synonyms.bx: 指突然解除某人的职务。

ex.chText: 他刚刚因为迟到被解雇。
ex.enText: He has just been fired/sacked for being late.

ex.chText: 公司把他开除了，他不知该怎么办。
ex.enText: The company fired/sacked him and he didn't know what to do.

synonyms.bx: 指强行解除某人的职务，常可与 sack 换用。

ex.chText: 这家连锁店10月份裁员500人。
ex.enText: The chain store laid off 500 workers in October.

ex.chText: 经济危机期间，数百万工人被解雇。
ex.enText: Millions of workers were laid off during the economic crisis.

synonyms.bx: 指因为没有工作可做而解雇员工。

ex.chText: 委员会罢免了那名腐败的官员。
ex.enText: The committee removed the corrupt official.
Congress has the right to remove the President from office.

synonyms.bx: 指免除某人的职务，尤指罢免身居要职者。

ex.chText: 他没做错事却被解雇了。
ex.enText: He was sacked from the job, although he did nothing wrong.

ex.chText: 爸爸因为喝醉酒而遭到解雇。
ex.enText: Dad was sacked for being drunk.

example: The President dissolved the parliament and called for new elections

tr: end one's encounter with somebody by causing or permitting the person to leave
example: I was dismissed after I gave my report

tr: discharge from an office or position
example: The boss fired his secretary today
The company terminated 25% of its workers
They dropped her after she had a child out of wedlock

value.def: If you dismiss something, you decide or say that it is not important enough for you to think about or consider.

example.ex: Mr Wakeham dismissed the reports as speculation...
example.tran: 韦克厄姆先生把这些报道当作臆测而不予考虑。

example.ex: I would certainly dismiss any allegations of impropriety by the Labour Party...
example.tran: 对于工党指责我行为不正当，我当然不会理会。

example.ex: I wouldn't dismiss it out of hand.
example.tran: 我不会不假思索地摈弃它。

value.def: If you dismiss something from your mind, you stop thinking about it.

example.ex: I dismissed him from my mind...
'It's been a lovely day,' she said, dismissing the episode.
example.tran: “这是开心的一天，”她说，将那事抛到了脑后。

value.tran: (从头脑中)去除;不再考虑;抛弃

value.def: When an employer dismisses an employee, the employer tells the employee that they are no longer needed to do the job that they have been doing.

example.ex: ...the power to dismiss civil servants who refuse to work...
example.tran: 开除拒不上班的公务员的权力

example.ex: The military commander has been dismissed.
example.tran: 军队司令已经被免职了。

value.def: If you are dismissed by someone in authority, they tell you that you can go away from them.

example.ex: Two more witnesses were called, heard and dismissed...
example.tran: 又有两个目击者被传唤，提供证言后获准退席。
雇来的马车被打发走了。

value.tran: 让…离去;把…打发走;解散;遣散

value.def: When a judge dismisses a case against someone, he or she formally states that there is no need for a trial, usually because there is not enough evidence for the case to continue.

example.ex: An American judge yesterday dismissed murder charges against Dr Jack Kevorkian.
example.tran: 昨天一个美国法官驳回了对杰克·凯沃尔基安医生的谋杀指控。

example.ex: ...their attempt to have the case against them dismissed.
example.tran: 想让指控他们的诉讼案被驳回的企图
